<br>
Anything that is done client side is hackable; and any game that sends data to the client (all of them) can have a program like Show EQ written for them (unless the data is heavily encrypted).  It's an unfortunate fact.  The only way to stop hackers is to store everything serverside (amazing server load to keep track of a players loc, speed, etc constantly) and have the data encrypted by 128 bit or better encryption (talk about lag <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).  Most likely TCP would also have to be used instead of UDP as well (holy cow that would hurt, just ask AO lol).<br>
